and
\pgfoffsetpath
?

A: My proposal:
spath3
and
nfold
.

Save the original path as
orig

Reverse
orig
, offset it and save it as
second
,

Area construction:
orig
, line to start of
second
, weld
second
, close.

Custom macro:
\borderpath{<border options>}{<path>}

\documentclass[tikz, border=5pt]{standalone}
\usetikzlibrary{patterns, nfold, spath3}
\makeatletter
\tikzset{offset now/.code=\pgfgetpath\tikz@temp\pgfsetpath\pgfutil@empty\pgfoffsetpath\tikz@temp{#1}}
\makeatother
\tikzset{
border/offset/.initial=-3mm,
border/main/.style={draw, line width=+1pt},
border/second/.style={draw, very thin},
border/area/.style={preaction={fill=white}, pattern=north west lines, pattern color=black!75},
%% Setters
% border/set main/.style={/tikz/border/main/.append style={#1}},
% border/set second/.style={/tikz/border/second/.append style={#1}},
% border/set area/.style={/tikz/border/area/.append style={#1}},
}
\NewDocumentCommand{\borderpath}{O{} m}{
\begin{scope}
\pgfqkeys{/tikz/border}{#1}
\path[path only]#2[spath/save=orig];
\path[path only, spath/use={orig, reverse}, offset now=\pgfkeysvalueof{/tikz/border/offset}, spath/save=second];
\path[border/area, spath/use=orig] -- (spath cs:{second} {0}) [spath/use={weld, second}] -- cycle;
\path[border/second, spath/use=second];
\path[border/main, spath/use=orig];
\end{scope}
}
\begin{document}
\begin{tikzpicture}
\draw[thick,teal] (-3,1) -- (3,1);
\borderpath{(-3,0) -- (-1,0) -- (-1,2) -- (1,2) -- (1,0) -- (3,0)}
\end{tikzpicture}
\end{document}

border
style on a path

Here's a
spath/offset={<source>}{<target>}{<length>}
key that offsets the path
<source>
about
<length>
and saves it as
<target>
.

The global version (
spath/offset global
) is only needed if the second path needs to be drawn. Otherwise the non-global
spath/offset
couldb be used and the second preaction should be removed. But I like the possibility to draw the parallel path differently.

The keys would accept
current
as the first argument (source) but I haven't tested it.
Using
current
as the second argument (target) won't do anything because it just saves the path and doesn't replace the actual current path.

The offsetting by
nfold
is put into a
pgfinterruptpath
environment which should make these pretty safe to use anyway not only in the context of preactions (where not much path-construction is happening usually).
Unfortunately, this needs a global scratch path name.

I've removed the
/tikz/border/main
part that was needed in the
\borderpath
macro since the path you use
border
on is the main path anyway and you can style that however you want with the normal interface.

Code

\documentclass[tikz, border=5pt]{standalone}
\usetikzlibrary{patterns, nfold, spath3}
%BEGIN_FOLD spath interface
\ExplSyntaxOn
\tikzset{
spath/offset/.code~n~args={3}{
\__tikzspath_maybe_current_path:nn {
\__tikzspath_check_path:nnn {
\__tikzspath_offset:nnnc {#2} {} {#3}
}
}{#1}{}},
spath/offset~global/.code~n~args={3}{
\__tikzspath_maybe_current_path:nn {
\__tikzspath_check_path:nnn {
\__tikzspath_offset:nnnc {#2} {~global} {#3}
}
}{#1}{}}}
\cs_set_eq:NN \__tikzspath_pgfoffsetpath:Nn \pgfoffsetpath % alias
\cs_new_protected_nopar:Npn \__tikzspath_offset:nnnN #1#2#3#4 {
\pgfinterruptpath
\__tikzspath_pgfoffsetpath:Nn #4 {#3}
\pgfkeysalso{/tikz/spath/clone~global={@@temp}{current}}
\endpgfinterruptpath
\pgfkeysalso{/tikz/spath/clone#2={#1}{@@temp}}
}
\cs_generate_variant:Nn \__tikzspath_offset:nnnN {nnnc}
\ExplSyntaxOff
%END_FOLD
%BEGIN_FOLD border interface
\tikzset{
border/.code={%
\pgfqkeys{/tikz/border}{#1}%
\tikzset{
preaction={
spath/clone={orig}{current},
spath/reverse=orig,
spath/offset global={orig}{second}{\pgfkeysvalueof{/tikz/border/offset}},
insert path={-- (spath cs:{second} {0})},
spath/use={weld, second},
spath/close,
border/area,
},
preaction={spath/use=second, border/second}}},
border/flip/.style={/tikz/border/offset/.expanded={-(\pgfkeysvalueof{/tikz/border/offset})}},
border/offset/.initial=5mm,
border/second/.code=, border/area/.code=,
}
%END_FOLD
\tikzset{
EDR/.style={
draw, line width=+1pt,
border={
area/.style={preaction={fill=white}, pattern=north west lines, pattern color=black!75},
offset=3mm,
#1}}}
\begin{document}
\begin{tikzpicture}
\draw[thick, teal] (-3,1) -- (3,1);
