gives in the PDF

URI(https://foo.com/extra/ui/command/Opt/ReportCmd.html)

The following is based on the response from @UrlikeFischer

\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{hyperref}
\ExplSyntaxOn
\cs_set_eq:NN\troytitlecase\text_titlecase_first:n
\ExplSyntaxOff
\newcommand{\varn}[1]{\texttt{#1}}
\newcommand\mcmd[2]
{\href{https://foo.com/extra/ui/command/#1/\troytitlecase{#2}Cmd.html}{#1.\varn{#2}}}
\begin{document}

\mcmd{Opt}{report}

\mcmd{Opt}{initCov}

\end{document}

which gives these URIs

https://foo.com/extra/ui/command/Opt/ReportCmd.html
https://foo.com/extra/ui/command/Opt/InitCovCmd.html

the first letter is capitalized and the remaining case is preserved. report -> Report, initCov -> InitCov

