\l_tmpb_box
\l_tmpa_box
{ 8ex }

\mode_leave_vertical:
\mark_insert:nn {dcp} { \g_dcp_first_box_mark_tl }
\box_use_drop:N \l_tmpb_box

\ExplSyntaxOff

How can I know what the last mark inserted before the split was so that I can
re-insert it after \verb+\l_tmpb_box+ is used?

\newpage

And similarly, how can I know what the first mark after the split was so that
I can re-insert it before \verb+\l_tmpa_box+ is used?

\ExplSyntaxOn

\mode_leave_vertical:
\box_use_drop:N \l_tmpa_box
\mark_insert:nn {dcp} { \g_dcp_last_box_mark_tl }

\ExplSyntaxOff

I can get the last mark in \verb+\l_tmpa_box+ by saving it globally.

