A: \mark_get_marks_for_reinsertion:nNN
extracts marks out of a
\vbox
but only those that are on top-level in that vbox, i.e., those that are in vertical mode there (including those that have been put in horizontal mode in a paragraph and then migrated out to vertical by TeX. What it doesn't see are those that are in restricted horizontal mode, e.g., in an
\hbox
and remain sitting there. In other words, it sees what TeX would put into
\splitfirstmark
and
\splitbotmark
when you split that vbox.

That is a basic restriction of TeX itself and not really possible to overcome (unless you use Lua directly and traverse the whole box content yourself, as suggested in the answer by Hans in a different answer to a different post, which is linked in a reply above).

As your code puts all the marks into hboxes they remain hidden.

