\usepackage{tikz}
%\definecolor{cadmiumgreen}{rgb}{0.0, 0.42, 0.235}
\definecolor{Gold}{RGB}{228,168,73}

\begin{document}
\thispagestyle{empty}
\begin{center}
\begin{tikzpicture}
\clip (0,0) ellipse[x radius=4.25cm, y radius=5.5cm];

%\fill[cadmiumgreen]
ellipse[x radius=4.25cm, y radius=5.5cm];
\node at (0,0) {\includegraphics[scale=1.31,clip, trim = 0 0 0 0]{example-image-a}};
\draw[line width=12pt,Gold!75!black] (225:4.25cm and 5.5cm) arc[start angle=225, end angle=-45, x radius=4.25cm, y radius=5.5cm];
\end{tikzpicture}
\end{center}
\end{document}

with the output:

QUESTION: How may I get the from to go around the ellipse
on the outside?
(In other words, I don't want any part of the interior of the elliptical image to be covered by the frame.)

Thank you.

A: The easiest way is to draw the frame first and before clipping. Then the clipped image will overlay the inner half of the frame width, but the outer half of that width will not be clipped away. So you will have
6pt
frame width entirely outside the clipped image.

% Source - https://tex.stackexchange.com/q/762891
% Posted by DDS, modified by community. See post 'Timeline' for change history
% Retrieved 2026-05-18, License - CC BY-SA 4.0

\documentclass[border=5pt]{standalone}
\usepackage{tikz}
\definecolor{Gold}{RGB}{228,168,73}
\begin{document}
\begin{tikzpicture}
\draw[line width=12pt,Gold!75!black] (225:4.25cm and 5.5cm) arc[start angle=225, end angle=-45, x radius=4.25cm, y radius=5.5cm];
\clip (0,0) ellipse[x radius=4.25cm, y radius=5.5cm];
\node at (0,0) {\includegraphics[scale=1.31,clip, trim = 0 0 0 0]{example-image-a}};
\end{tikzpicture}
\end{document}

If this is not an option because you are clipping something which does not fill the ellipse, for instance, you would need to adjust the radii for the frame and clip it separately to get the same effect.

% Source - https://tex.stackexchange.com/q/762891
% Posted by DDS, modified by community. See post 'Timeline' for change history
% Retrieved 2026-05-18, License - CC BY-SA 4.0

\documentclass[border=5pt]{standalone}
\usepackage{tikz}
\definecolor{Gold}{RGB}{228,168,73}
\begin{document}
\begin{tikzpicture}
\draw[line width=6pt,Gold!75!black] (225:4.25cm + 3pt and 5.5cm + 3pt)
arc[start angle=225, end angle=-45, x radius=4.25cm + 3pt, y radius=5.5cm + 3pt];
\clip (0,0) ellipse[x radius=4.25cm, y radius=5.5cm];
\node at (0,0) {\includegraphics[scale=0.31,clip, trim = 0 0 0 0]{example-image-a}};
\end{tikzpicture}
