A: You must load the
colortbl
package if you want to use its macros
\rowcolor
,
\columncolor
, and
\cellcolor
.

Assuming your TeX distribution is reasonably up to date, you can load the
colortbl
package in two different ways:

Load the package directly, i.e., run
\usepackage{colortbl}
in the preamble.

Load it indirectly by specifying the
table
option when loading the
xcolor
package:
\usepackage[table]{xcolor}
.

If your TeX distribution is more than two years out of date, you should probably use the second option.

Off-topic: The
geometry
package's
top=2cm, bottom=2cm, left=1.5cm, right=1.5cm
options may be stated more succinctly as
vmargin=2cm, hmargin=1.5cm
.

