The other link above allows the root node to have an icon also.

Since your code already answers the question asked, I was not very interested in that question, so I decided to reorganise the code instead. In particular, I wanted a style which would automatically add the labels and get them left-aligned in a block and horizontally aligned with the nodes they describe.

I don't think tabulars are a good option here as the result looks very messy to me. However, if you do want tabulars, you can just use
align={<column spec>}
