Q: I have a macro for typesetting Attribute Value Matrices (AVMs). Sometimes I want to add a little bit of vertical space. My understanding is that I type
\\[2mm]
and then 2mm space is inserted. But this is not what happens. Sometimes I have to add 8mm or 10 or 12. It somehow seems to depend on what happened before. But why? And how does it work and is there anything I can do to get the desired behavior?

\documentclass{scrartcl}

\usepackage{etex}

\usepackage{array}

