A: \\[10pt]
won't have any effect if the depth of the row is already
10pt
more than the normal baseline depth. The optional argument is added to the depth of the struct added to each row.

You can use
booktabs
spacing commands or here a custom
\addrowspace
command to add a fixed amount of space. (LaTeX doesn't do this by default as it would break vertical rules).

I simplified the code a bit, perhaps too much in some places as it wasn't always clear what the intention is, but

\documentclass{scrartcl}

% not etex (unless your latex is more than 10 years old)

\usepackage{array}
\usepackage{yhmath}% bigger <>

%upfont nont needed
\newcommand{\nliste}[1]{%
\mbox{$\langle$\normalfont#1$\rangle$}%
}

%leftright not needed
\newcommand{\eliste}{\mbox{$\langle\rangle$}}

\NewDocumentCommand{\ms}{om}{%
\mbox{%
\delimiterfactor=1000 \delimitershortfall=0pt\tabcolsep=0pt%
$\hspace{-2pt}\left[%
\begin{tabular}{>{\upshape\scshape}l@{}>{\hspace*{5pt}\normalfont\itshape}l}
\IfNoValueF{#1}{%
\multicolumn{2}{>{\normalfont\itshape}l}{#1}%
\\}%
#2%
\end{tabular}%
\right]\hspace{-2pt}$%
}%
% \par\vspace{1mm}%
\vspace{1mm}%
}

\newcommand{\ibox}[1]{{%
\setlength{\fboxsep}{1.25pt}%
\fbox{$\scriptstyle #1$}%
}}

\newcommand{\liste}[1]{%
\mbox{%
$%
\left\langle\mbox{\upshape\normalfont#1}\right\rangle%
$%
}%\\[2pt]%
}

\newcommand{\ind}[1]{\mbox{$_{\ibox{#1}}$}}

\newcommand\addrowspace[1]{\noalign{\vspace{#1}}}
\begin{document}

\ms{
\ldots & \ms{ cat & \ms{% head & verb \\
arg-st & \ibox{1} $\oplus$ \ibox{2} $\oplus$ \nliste{ V[\textit{inf},
\textsc{lex}+, \textsc{subj}~\ibox{1}, \textsc{comps}~\ibox{2}, \textsc{ltop} \ibox{3} ] } }\\
cont & \ms{
ltop & \ibox{4}\\
ind & \ibox{5} event } }\\
\addrowspace{10pt}
rels & \liste{ \ms[scheinen]{
lbl & \ibox{4}\\
arg0 & \ibox{5}\\
arg1 & \ibox{6}\\
} }\\
\addrowspace{10pt}
hcons & \liste{ \ms[qeq]{
harg & \ibox{6}\\
larg & \ibox{3}} }
}

\end{document}

Q: When I open the pdf of my MWE in Adobe Acrobat and try to sign the signature field, I get the error 2013 which warns me that my fonts are not embedded. To be more precise, it's the Helvetica font that's not embedded.

I thought that compiling with LuaLaTeX would make all my fonts embedded, but that's not the case.

I assume that Helvetica is used by the \textfieldnew command, despite
f.textFont = 'ArialMT'
.

\documentclass[
a4paper,
fontsize=10pt
headsepline=0.4pt
]{scrartcl}

\usepackage[english, main=ngerman, shorthands=off]{babel}
\usepackage{fontspec}

\setmainfont{Arial}
\setsansfont{Arial}

\usepackage{eforms}

\begin{document}

\newcommand{\textfield}[5]{
\edef\Titel{#2}
\TextField[name=#1, width=#3, charsize=10pt, height=1em, format = { var f = this.getField('#1'); f.textFont = 'ArialMT';}, #4]{}#5
}
\newcommand{\textfieldnew}[5]{%
\edef\Titel{#2}%
\TextField[name=#1, width=#3, charsize=10pt, height=1em, format = { var f = this.getField('#1'); f.textFont = 'ArialMT';}, #4]{}%
#5%
}

\textfieldnew{Test}{}{7.5cm}{default={Test}, onblur={this.getField('TestEN').value = event.value;}}{}

\sigField{Signatur1}{7.5cm}{1.2cm}

\end{document}

Is there any way to embed the fonts in LaTeX or change the font of the textfields? Doing it in Adobe Acrobat is no option for me.

A: As written in my comment the l3pdffield package doesn't use Helvetica as fallback.

There is no dedicated module for signature fields yet, but actually they are quite simple fields, you only need to set the right keys. You can get more info about the various commands and keys in the various l3pdffield-XXX.pdf.
texdoc -l l3pdffield
should give you a list.

\RequirePackage{pdfmanagement}
\documentclass[
a4paper,
fontsize=10pt
headsepline=0.4pt
]{scrartcl}

\usepackage[english, main=ngerman, shorthands=off]{babel}
\usepackage{fontspec}

\setmainfont{Arial}
\setsansfont{Arial}

\usepackage{l3pdffield}

\begin{document}

\ExplSyntaxOn
\pdffield_textfield:n {name=text,font=arial}

\par

\pdffield_field:nn{name=signature,FT=Sig,Q=left}{mysig}
\fbox{\pdffield_annot:n{width=3cm,height=2cm,parent=mysig}}
\ExplSyntaxOff
\end{document}
